 it says `OK`, the token format is accepted and auth likely works.\n\n2. **Probe gateway + channel warnings**\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway probe\n```\nThis catches config issues that can look like token problems (like your group allowlist warning).\n\n3. **Verify token directly with Telegram**\nIn a browser, open:\n```text\nhttps://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_TOKEN>/getMe\n```\nIf token is valid, you get JSON with `\"ok\": true` and bot info.  \nIf wrong, youвҖҷll get `\"ok\": false` (unauthorized).\n\n4. **Confirm the exact env var OpenClaw is using**\nOn PowerShell:\n```powershell\n$env:TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n```\nMake sure this matches the token from BotFather exactly (no extra spaces/newlines).\n\n---\n\nIf you want, paste your `openclaw status` Channels section (redacted), and IвҖҷll tell you in 10 seconds whether token vs config is the issue.","textSignature":"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8b374884481939c8cacdff9267fc7"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":1758,"output":345,"cacheRead":10112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12215,"cost":{"input":0.0030765,"output":0.00483,"cacheRead":0.0017695999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0096761}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772663665123}}
