,\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_BtWAjGrqF2g0hkCJvfAXXPca|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8b9a120748193b338add80b239942\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"Get-Item C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\openclaw_backup_20260304_1536.zip | Select-Object Length,LastWriteTime\",\n            \"workdir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\"\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"Get-Item C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\tonyb\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace\\\\\\\\openclaw_backup_20260304_1536.zip | Select-Object Length,LastWriteTime\\\",\\\"workdir\\\":\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\tonyb\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace\\\"}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665247503\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Reporting partial download status**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Got it вҖ” IвҖҷm on it.\\n\\nI successfully pulled the **actual Drive download** (not the preview page), and itвҖҷs actively downloading now.  \\nYour backup is large (**~3.8 GB**), and I can already see the file growing locally (currently ~54 MB and increasing), so this part is working.\\n\\nAlso, the вҖңgateway restart timed outвҖқ message is because:\\n- one `node.exe` already had port `18789` open\\n- so the scheduled task restart step failed, **but the gateway itself is still reachable and working**\\n\\nIвҖҷll continue with the backup import once the download finishes.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8b9ab413c8193847d3f0783cda573\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665253561\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"ok keep backing up and will we be able to hook up to both computere\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665335143\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Polling process status**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_jGjSdHTTM04DRtIyRWOwZRKB|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8b9fa1d20819389927af719f7cfcf\",\n          \"name\": \"process\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"poll\",\n            \"sessionId\": \"grand-meadow\",\n            \"timeout\": 1000\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"action\\\":\\\"poll\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"grand-meadow\\\",\\\"timeout\\\":1000}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665335146\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying node pairing and gateway setup**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Yep вҖ” IвҖҷll keep the backup download running in the background.\\n\\nAnd **yes**, we can hook up to **both computers**.  \\nBest setup is:\\n\\n- Pick this one as the **main gateway**\\n- Pair each computer as a **node/device** to it\\n- Then I can check/control both from one place\\n\\nSo: one вҖңbrain,вҖқ multiple machines attached.  \\nOnce this backup finishes, IвҖҷll move straight to the dual-computer hookup flow.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8b9fd78148193b5649d81e8ee0d92\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665340253\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"what are we dong\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665501534\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Right now, weвҖҷre doing 3 things:\\n\\n1. **Fixed your Telegram token/setup**  \\n   - Token is valid, bot is connected.\\n\\n2. **Downloading your Google Drive backup** (`openclaw_backup_20260304_1536.zip`)  \\n   - ItвҖҷs a large file (~3.8 GB), still in progress.\\n\\n3. **Preparing multi-computer setup**  \\n   - Goal: this PC as main, both computers connected to it.\\n\\nSo short version: **stabilize bot вҶ’ finish backup restore file вҶ’ connect both computers under one main system.**\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8ba9e403081939e8d01117916891e\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665501537\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"stabilize bot вҶ’ finish backup restore file вҶ’ connect both computers under one main system. what do i need to do hwer\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665550129\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Providing concise next steps**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Perfect вҖ” hereвҖҷs exactly what **you** need to do right now:\\n\\n### Right now (while backup downloads)\\n1. **Keep this laptop awake + online**\\n   - DonвҖҷt sleep/restart it.\\n2. **Leave OpenClaw running**\\n   - DonвҖҷt close terminal/app.\\n\\n### For bot stabilization (you can do now)\\n3. In Telegram, send your bot a DM:  \\n   **`ping`**\\n4. Tell me if it replies.\\n   - If no reply, IвҖҷll run live logs next.\\n\\n### For connecting both computers\\n5. On the **second computer**, install/open OpenClaw.\\n6. Start node/device pairing on that computer.\\n7. Send me вҖңpairing startedвҖқ (or the code/request shown).\\n\\nOnce you do #7, IвҖҷll handle approval and hook both systems into the same main setup.\\n\\nIf you want, I can give you a super short вҖңcopy/paste commands onlyвҖқ version next.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bad0da6c81938290a52da5e9a4cd\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665550134\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"the other computer is the main and i want to make teh desktop i'm typing on here the main\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665582758\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Providing migration steps and commands**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Got it вҖ” weвҖҷre **flipping roles**:\\n\\n- Old laptop = currently main  \\n- This desktop = new main вң…\\n\\nHereвҖҷs what to do in order:\\n\\n1. **On this desktop (new main):**\\n   - Keep OpenClaw/gateway running (already mostly good).\\n   - Keep internet on.\\n\\n2. **On old laptop (current main):**\\n   - Open OpenClaw.\\n   - Start **node pairing** toward this desktopвҖҷs gateway (or run device/pairing flow from `openclaw devices --help` if needed).\\n\\n3. **On this desktop:**\\n   - Approve the incoming pairing request.\\n   - After approval, old laptop becomes a connected node to this desktop.\\n\\n4. **Test both:**\\n   - Send bot a DM (вҖңpingвҖқ).\\n   - Verify this desktop responds as main.\\n   - Then verify we can query/control the old laptop node.\\n\\nIf you want, I can walk command-by-command live right now while you do it.  \\nStart with old laptop and say: **вҖңpairing screen openвҖқ** when youвҖҷre there.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8baf15114819385a806df3d8060b0\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665582762\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"i have the screens open\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665693913\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Suggesting next steps without tools**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Perfect. Do this now on the **old laptop**:\\n\\n1. In terminal, run:\\n```bash\\nopenclaw devices --help\\n```\\n2. Then run the pairing/start command it shows (usually under pair/connect).\\n3. Keep that screen open and tell me what it prints (pairing code or pending request ID).\\n\\nAs soon as you paste that, IвҖҷll guide the exact approve step on this desktop and finish the main-switch.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bb60ba508193a9c837ce57a59abd\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665693918\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"tell me what to do. on hee\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665795117\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" On **this desktop (here)**, do exactly this in PowerShell:\\n\\n```powershell\\nopenclaw pairing pending\\n```\\n\\nIf it shows a request, approve it with:\\n\\n```powershell\\nopenclaw pairing approve <REQUEST_ID>\\n```\\n\\nThen verify connection:\\n\\n```powershell\\nopenclaw nodes list\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\nIf `pairing pending` shows nothing, then the old laptop hasnвҖҷt sent the request yet.  \\nIn that case, on the old laptop run:\\n\\n```powershell\\nopenclaw pairing request\\n```\\n\\n(Or `openclaw devices --help` and use the pair/request command it shows), then come back here and run `openclaw pairing pending` again.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bbc6a1c48193983cb3829838bdb5\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665795121\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"it says you need to ask openclaw devices list\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665824369\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Running device list command**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_6XgcpKbcEOKWK7gDdJOvIgSb|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bbe240f08193b6592556836911b3\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"openclaw devices list\",\n            \"workdir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 120000\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"openclaw devices list\\\",\\\"workdir\\\":\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\tonyb\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace\\\",\\\"yieldMs\\\":120000}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665824373\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Suggesting device identification steps**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Yep вҖ” do that. On this machine, run:\\n\\n```powershell\\nopenclaw devices list\\n```\\n\\nI just checked here and it already shows **2 paired devices**, so pairing is basically in place.\\n\\n### Next step to make **this desktop** the true main\\nOn the **old laptop**, stop its gateway so it doesnвҖҷt compete as main:\\n\\n```powershell\\nopenclaw gateway stop\\n```\\n\\nThen on **this desktop** confirm main is healthy:\\n\\n```powershell\\nopenclaw status\\n```\\n\\nIf you paste both outputs, IвҖҷll confirm the switch is complete.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bbedda408193b3dab322596f33dc\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665835683\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"i'm doing it now and now do this openclaw status\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665924562\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_U77TkfiJT0lSpzN606OJaVRT|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bc45f76481939de7e7ef923fd429\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"openclaw status\",\n            \"workdir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 120000\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"openclaw status\\\",\\\"workdir\\\":\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\tonyb\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace\\\",\\\"yieldMs\\\":120000}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665924566\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Ran it вҖ” this desktop looks good as main.\\n\\nKey points:\\n- **Gateway is reachable** on this desktop (`ws://127.0.0.1:18789`)\\n- **Telegram is ON / OK**\\n- **Main session active just now**\\n\\nOnly warning worth deciding on:\\n- `dmPolicy=\\\"open\\\"` means anyone can DM the bot.\\n\\nIf you want safer setup, I can switch DMs back to pairing/allowlist after we finish migration. For now, main switch is working.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bc52dea48193b39409f4991d3e28\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665938124\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"what's the main computert\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665977540\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Right now, **this desktop youвҖҷre typing on** is acting as main.\\n\\nWhy:\\n- This machineвҖҷs gateway is reachable\\n- Telegram channel is connected here\\n- Main session is active here now\\n\\nSo yes вҖ” **desktop = main computer** at the moment.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bc843aac819391329a38122a8135\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772665977543\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"now can we get everything up to date iwht both files. will the files be uploading on both at all times\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666045131\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying file sync approach**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Short answer: **not automatically, not by default**.\\n\\nOpenClaw does **not** continuously mirror all files between both computers on its own.  \\nEach machine has its own local files unless we set up sync.\\n\\n### If you want вҖңalways up to date on bothвҖқ\\nPick one of these:\\n\\n1. **Git repo sync** (best for configs/docs/code)\\n   - Commit/push on main, pull on other machine.\\n2. **Cloud folder sync** (Google Drive/OneDrive/Dropbox)\\n   - Put shared files in synced folder.\\n3. **Scheduled backup/rsync job**\\n   - Periodic copy from main вҶ’ second machine.\\n\\n### Recommended for your setup\\n- Keep this desktop as **source of truth (main)**.\\n- Sync only key paths (not whole system blindly), e.g.:\\n  - `C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace`\\n  - optionally selected `.openclaw` config/state files\\n\\nIf you want, I can give you the exact step-by-step for **OneDrive sync** or **Git sync** right now (your choice).\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bcbf245c8193b58ee082643be1b9\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666045135\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Yep вҖ” thatвҖҷs expected right now. ItвҖҷs saying that because the switch isnвҖҷt fully completed yet. To finish the handoff: On desktop: openclaw gateway start Pair laptop to desktop gateway On desktop: openclaw devices list вҶ’ openclaw devices approve Test a ping/DM After that, desktop is truly main.are you seein ok this is what the laptop says\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666119635\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Yep, I see it вҖ” and that message is basically correct guidance.\\n\\nFrom what I can see on desktop, youвҖҷre already very close:\\n- Desktop gateway is up/reachable\\n- Devices are already paired/listed\\n- Telegram is connected on desktop\\n\\nSo you likely just need the **final validation** step, not full re-pair from scratch.\\n\\nDo this now:\\n1. On desktop: `openclaw devices list`\\n2. In Telegram DM your bot: `ping`\\n3. Confirm reply comes from this desktop session\\n\\nIf ping works, handoff is complete and desktop is main.  \\nIf ping fails, IвҖҷll run live logs immediately and fix it with you.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd08f4448193b9163f9b6cb3cd28\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666119639\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"ok do it\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666134244\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_YvheKp0pZI7wuvKIFZCELFD3|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd17d7648193a6d1a946436c442d\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"openclaw devices list\",\n            \"workdir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 120000\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"openclaw devices list\\\",\\\"workdir\\\":\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\tonyb\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace\\\",\\\"yieldMs\\\":120000}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666134249\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Considering ping via message tool**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_pUz7GR6ZiWalDbauKtAOFnAB|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd2297c0819385ecdfee1de01bd7\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"openclaw status --deep\",\n            \"workdir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 120000\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"openclaw status --deep\\\",\\\"workdir\\\":\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\tonyb\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace\\\",\\\"yieldMs\\\":120000}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666142653\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Requesting user ping**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Done вҖ” I ran it.\\n\\n- `openclaw devices list` вҶ’ **Paired (2)** вң…  \\n- `openclaw status --deep` вҶ’ Gateway reachable + **Telegram health OK** вң…\\n\\nSo desktop side looks good.  \\nNow final live check: send `ping` to your bot in Telegram and tell me what it replies.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd30788081938886e13b64ba330b\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666158579\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"are all the files matching on both\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666188090\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Checking paired nodes status**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_CTw3C8QEajzOMm9qCSja95jd|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd4e2ca4819384f6b62ad69a9bba\",\n          \"name\": \"nodes\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"status\"\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"action\\\":\\\"status\\\"}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666188093\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Not yet вҖ” I **canвҖҷt confirm file matching** right now.\\n\\nWhy:\\n- I can see paired **devices**, but I still donвҖҷt see active **nodes** to inspect files (`nodes: []`), so thereвҖҷs no live file comparison channel yet.\\n\\nSo at this moment, assume:\\n- Bot/gateway is working on desktop\\n- File sync between both machines is **not guaranteed**\\n\\nIf you want true вҖңmatching files,вҖқ we need to set up one sync method (Git, OneDrive/Drive sync, or scheduled copy) and then verify with checksums.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd503c6881939bb9a35e35145778\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666191365\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"cn you please do it\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666252604\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Planning local sync setup with limitations**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Yes вҖ” I can do most of it now, but I need **one thing** from you first:\\n\\n### I need one choice:\\nPick sync method:\\n1. **OneDrive/Google Drive folder sync** (easiest, near real-time)\\n2. **LAN mirror with `robocopy`** (good if both PCs on same network)\\n3. **Git sync** (best for text/config only)\\n\\nGiven your goal (вҖңboth always matchingвҖқ), I recommend **#1 cloud folder sync**.\\n\\nIf you say **вҖңuse OneDriveвҖқ** (or Google Drive), IвҖҷll set this desktop side immediately and give you the exact 2 commands to run on the laptop so both stay synced.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd909fd08193b9570cb0620b4619\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666252608\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"google drive i'm not sure wht to do\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666275163\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Guiding Google Drive setup**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" Perfect вҖ” letвҖҷs do **Google Drive sync** the easy way.\\n\\n### Goal\\nKeep this folder synced on both computers:\\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### On **both computers** (desktop + laptop)\\n\\n1. Install/open **Google Drive for desktop**  \\n2. Sign into the **same Google account**  \\n3. Wait until Drive shows as connected\\n\\n---\\n\\n### On this desktop (main)\\n\\n1. Open File Explorer and go to:\\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace`\\n2. Right-click `workspace` вҶ’ **Copy**\\n3. Go to:\\n`G:\\\\My Drive\\\\` (or вҖңGoogle Drive\\\\My DriveвҖқ)\\n4. Paste as:\\n`G:\\\\My Drive\\\\openclaw-workspace-main`\\n\\nWait for upload to finish (cloud icon becomes check).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### On laptop\\n\\n1. Open:\\n`G:\\\\My Drive\\\\openclaw-workspace-main`\\n2. Copy that folder to:\\n`C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace`\\n3. If asked overwrite/merge, choose **Replace** (after backup if needed).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Important\\n- DonвҖҷt edit both PCs at the exact same time in same file (can cause conflict copies).\\n- Use desktop as primary editor when possible.\\n\\n---\\n\\nIf you want, next IвҖҷll give you a **safe merge checklist** so nothing important gets overwritten when you replace laptop files.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bdaa6d508193824d54a777b83142\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666275168\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"i'm going to ell the laptop now to do this can you do the same\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772666326191\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Attempting local file operations**\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_KDyCxpIkcCn0r3uESM96Rs1M|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bdd991788193b024de64ab31f4ed\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"$src='C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace'; $dstRoot='G:\\\\My Drive'; if(Test-Path $dstRoot){ $dst=Join-Path $dstRoot 'openclaw-workspace-main'; New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $dst -Force | Out-Null; robocopy $src $dst /E /R:1 /W:1 /NFL /NDL /NP /NJH /NJS; Write-Output \\\"SYNCED_TO: $dst\\\" } else { Write-Output 'GOOGLE_DRIVE_NOT_FOUND' }\",\n            \"workdir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 120000\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"$src='C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\tonyb\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace'; $dstRoot='G:\\\\\\\\My Drive'; if(Test-Path $dstRoot){ $dst=Join-Path $dstRoot 'openclaw-workspace-main'; New-Item -I