,"text":" Short answer: **not automatically, not by default**.\n\nOpenClaw does **not** continuously mirror all files between both computers on its own.  \nEach machine has its own local files unless we set up sync.\n\n### If you want вҖңalways up to date on bothвҖқ\nPick one of these:\n\n1. **Git repo sync** (best for configs/docs/code)\n   - Commit/push on main, pull on other machine.\n2. **Cloud folder sync** (Google Drive/OneDrive/Dropbox)\n   - Put shared files in synced folder.\n3. **Scheduled backup/rsync job**\n   - Periodic copy from main вҶ’ second machine.\n\n### Recommended for your setup\n- Keep this desktop as **source of truth (main)**.\n- Sync only key paths (not whole system blindly), e.g.:\n  - `C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace`\n  - optionally selected `.openclaw` config/state files\n\nIf you want, I can give you the exact step-by-step for **OneDrive sync** or **Git sync** right now (your choice).","textSignature":"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bcbf245c8193b58ee082643be1b9"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772666045135},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yep вҖ” thatвҖҷs expected right now. ItвҖҷs saying that because the switch isnвҖҷt fully completed yet. To finish the handoff: On desktop: openclaw gateway start Pair laptop to desktop gateway On desktop: openclaw devices list вҶ’ openclaw devices approve Test a ping/DM After that, desktop is truly main.are you seein ok this is what the laptop says"}],"timestamp":1772666119635},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":""},{"type":"text","text":" Yep, I see it вҖ” and that message is basically correct guidance.\n\nFrom what I can see on desktop, youвҖҷre already very close:\n- Desktop gateway is up/reachable\n- Devices are already paired/listed\n- Telegram is connected on desktop\n\nSo you likely just need the **final validation** step, not full re-pair from scratch.\n\nDo this now:\n1. On desktop: `openclaw devices list`\n2. In Telegram DM your bot: `ping`\n3. Confirm reply comes from this desktop session\n\nIf ping works, handoff is complete and desktop is main.  \nIf ping fails, IвҖҷll run live logs immediately and fix it with you.","textSignature":"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd08f4448193b9163f9b6cb3cd28"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772666119639},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok do it"}],"timestamp":1772666134244},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_YvheKp0pZI7wuvKIFZCELFD3|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd17d7648193a6d1a946436c442d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw devices list","workdir":"C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":120000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw devices list\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":120000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772666134249},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering ping via message tool**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_pUz7GR6ZiWalDbauKtAOFnAB|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd2297c0819385ecdfee1de01bd7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status --deep","workdir":"C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":120000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw status --deep\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":120000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772666142653},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Requesting user ping**"},{"type":"text","text":" Done вҖ” I ran it.\n\n- `openclaw devices list` вҶ’ **Paired (2)** вң…  \n- `openclaw status --deep` вҶ’ Gateway reachable + **Telegram health OK** вң…\n\nSo desktop side looks good.  \nNow final live check: send `ping` to your bot in Telegram and tell me what it replies.","textSignature":"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd30788081938886e13b64ba330b"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772666158579},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"are all the files matching on both"}],"timestamp":1772666188090},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Checking paired nodes status**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_CTw3C8QEajzOMm9qCSja95jd|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd4e2ca4819384f6b62ad69a9bba","name":"nodes","arguments":{"action":"status"},"partialJson":"{\"action\":\"status\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772666188093},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":""},{"type":"text","text":" Not yet вҖ” I **canвҖҷt confirm file matching** right now.\n\nWhy:\n- I can see paired **devices**, but I still donвҖҷt see active **nodes** to inspect files (`nodes: []`), so thereвҖҷs no live file comparison channel yet.\n\nSo at this moment, assume:\n- Bot/gateway is working on desktop\n- File sync between both machines is **not guaranteed**\n\nIf you want true вҖңmatching files,вҖқ we need to set up one sync method (Git, OneDrive/Drive sync, or scheduled copy) and then verify with checksums.","textSignature":"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd503c6881939bb9a35e35145778"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772666191365},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"cn you please do it"}],"timestamp":1772666252604},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning local sync setup with limitations**"},{"type":"text","text":" Yes вҖ” I can do most of it now, but I need **one thing** from you first:\n\n### I need one choice:\nPick sync method:\n1. **OneDrive/Google Drive folder sync** (easiest, near real-time)\n2. **LAN mirror with `robocopy`** (good if both PCs on same network)\n3. **Git sync** (best for text/config only)\n\nGiven your goal (вҖңboth always matchingвҖқ), I recommend **#1 cloud folder sync**.\n\nIf you say **вҖңuse OneDriveвҖқ** (or Google Drive), IвҖҷll set this desktop side immediately and give you the exact 2 commands to run on the laptop so both stay synced.","textSignature":"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bd909fd08193b9570cb0620b4619"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772666252608},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"google drive i'm not sure wht to do"}],"timestamp":1772666275163},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Guiding Google Drive setup**"},{"type":"text","text":" Perfect вҖ” letвҖҷs do **Google Drive sync** the easy way.\n\n### Goal\nKeep this folder synced on both computers:\n`C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace`\n\n---\n\n### On **both computers** (desktop + laptop)\n\n1. Install/open **Google Drive for desktop**  \n2. Sign into the **same Google account**  \n3. Wait until Drive shows as connected\n\n---\n\n### On this desktop (main)\n\n1. Open File Explorer and go to:\n`C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace`\n2. Right-click `workspace` вҶ’ **Copy**\n3. Go to:\n`G:\\My Drive\\` (or вҖңGoogle Drive\\My DriveвҖқ)\n4. Paste as:\n`G:\\My Drive\\openclaw-workspace-main`\n\nWait for upload to finish (cloud icon becomes check).\n\n---\n\n### On laptop\n\n1. Open:\n`G:\\My Drive\\openclaw-workspace-main`\n2. Copy that folder to:\n`C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace`\n3. If asked overwrite/merge, choose **Replace** (after backup if needed).\n\n---\n\n### Important\n- DonвҖҷt edit both PCs at the exact same time in same file (can cause conflict copies).\n- Use desktop as primary editor when possible.\n\n---\n\nIf you want, next IвҖҷll give you a **safe merge checklist** so nothing important gets overwritten when you replace laptop files.","textSignature":"msg_016894fb01b951d60169a8bdaa6d508193824d54a777b83142"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772666275168},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"i'm going to ell the laptop now to do this can you do the same"}],"timestamp":1772666326191},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Attempting local file operations**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_KDyCxpIkcCn0r3uESM96Rs1M|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bdd991788193b024de64ab31f4ed","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$src='C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace'; $dstRoot='G:\\My Drive'; if(Test-Path $dstRoot){ $dst=Join-Path $dstRoot 'openclaw-workspace-main'; New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $dst -Force | Out-Null; robocopy $src $dst /E /R:1 /W:1 /NFL /NDL /NP /NJH /NJS; Write-Output \"SYNCED_TO: $dst\" } else { Write-Output 'GOOGLE_DRIVE_NOT_FOUND' }","workdir":"C:\\Users\\tonyb\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":120000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"$src='C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace'; $dstRoot='G:\\\\My Drive'; if(Test-Path $dstRoot){ $dst=Join-Path $dstRoot 'openclaw-workspace-main'; New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $dst -Force | Out-Null; robocopy $src $dst /E /R:1 /W:1 /NFL /NDL /NP /NJH /NJS; Write-Output \\\"SYNCED_TO: $dst\\\" } else { Write-Output 'GOOGLE_DRIVE_NOT_FOUND' }\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\tonyb\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":120000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772666326195},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Checking alternative Google Drive paths**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1R3XafRbOvzhgVY51AyNjQKL|fc_016894fb01b951d60169a8bde0c7048193b5825ea4e5908043","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$paths=@('G:\\My Drive','G: